<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine - Model Years Late 1997 to 2003 - Crankcase, Crankshaft, Connecting
        Rods, And Pistons - Flywheel and Flywheel Housing - Check Flywheel Housing Bore Concentricity
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Check Flywheel Housing Bore Concentricity</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Bore concentricity and face runout checks are performed to ensure proper engine to transmission
                    alignment. Improper bore concentricity and face runout may result in reduced transmission life.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f1200707" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg6/EG6494.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Checking the Flywheel Housing Bore Concentricity</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Dial Indicator</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Indicator Tip</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Magnetic Base</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach a dial indicator magnetic base to the crankshaft and place the indicator tip against
                the flywheel housing bore.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Zero the dial indicator.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rotate the crankshaft slowly and record the total indicator variation. Compare the result to
                the specification for flywheel housing bore concentricity.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
